## Lovable в†’ React Native Translation Reference

When referencing the Lovable web prototype, apply these conversions:
| Lovable (web) | GymCrush (RN) |
|---|---|
| `<div>` | `<View>` |
| `<span>`, `<p>`, `<h1>`вЂ“`<h6>` | `<Text>` |
| `<button>` | `<Pressable>` |
| `<img>` | `<Image>` from `expo-image` |
| `<input>` | `<TextInput>` |
| `<a>` | `<Link>` from expo-router or `<Pressable>` |
| `<header>`, `<main>`, `<section>` | `<View>` |
| `overflow-y-auto` | `<ScrollView>` |
| `min-h-screen` | `style={{ flex: 1 }}` or `layout.flex1` |
| `sticky top-0` | Fixed position via flex layout |
| `backdrop-blur-sm` | `<BlurView>` from `expo-blur` or skip |
| `onClick` | `onPress` |
| `hover:` classes | Remove (no hover on mobile) |
| `cursor-pointer` | Remove |
| `safe-top` / `safe-bottom` | `<SafeAreaView>` |
| `animate-fade-in` etc. | Reanimated `FadeIn`, `SlideInUp` entering animations |
| `shadow-card` | `style={shadows.card}` from `@/theme` |
| CSS `linear-gradient()` | `<LinearGradient>` from `expo-linear-gradient` with `gradients.*` from `@/theme` |
| `lucide-react` | `lucide-react-native` |
| shadcn `<Button>` | Custom `<Button>` in `components/ui/Button.tsx` |
| shadcn `<Input>` | Custom `<Input>` in `components/ui/Input.tsx` |
